content:
Create, edit, and delete multiple Salesforce or external records on one page using Edit Block. For example, if you are collecting an Account's Contact information, you can add an Edit Block to your OmniScript to enable users to add a record for each Contact.

In the Summer '17 version, the first three fields of the Edit Block display by default. In Winter '18, the display fields must be chosen by the user when configuring the Edit Block in the OmniScript Designer.

When you disable an active OmniScript with an Edit Block created before Winter '18, you must determine which fields you want to display on the Edit Block before reactivating the OmniScript.

Select an Edit Mode and configure the Edit Block to display elements.

Add Inputs to an Edit Block: Enter data into Input elements for editing fields in records.

Configure an Edit Block: Enable a user to add and edit multiple entries in a single array, prefilling repeatable blocks with data using an array format.

Add, Edit, and Delete Records with Edit Block Actions: Enable users to add, edit, and delete records by using Edit Block's default remote actions, adding custom functionality by configuring additional actions.

Display Sprites in an Edit Block: Display sprites to indicate information about an Edit Block record entry using the Default Svg Sprite and Default Svg Icon properties.

Set a Select Mode in Edit Block: Enable users to change an Edit Block entry's boolean value by clicking on Edit Block entries.

Work with Formulas in Edit Block: Perform equations and combine strings by using Formula Elements, placing formulas within an Edit Block to access element values.

Override an Edit Block LWC: Apply custom code to an Edit Block by extending and overriding the Edit Block's lightning web components.
title: Understanding OmniStudio's Edit Block Feature
